<br>
The best available tank.<br>
The best available healer.<br>
The best available crowd control / damage mitigation / buffage.<br>
The best available damage dealers.<br>
<br>
If you're going deep in a dungeon, you might put a wizard or druid in a &quot;damage dealer&quot; slot.  Preferably a druid, really, because then you also have extra healing, damage shield and snare.<br>
<br>
You might also put a ranger in a damage dealer slot, especially if you don't have a druid for the snare ability.<br>
<br>
So usually that's:<br>
1) Warrior<br>
2) Cleric<br>
3) Enchanter<br>
4) Rogue/monk<br>
5) Rogue/monk/ranger<br>
6) Rogue/monk/wizard/druid<br>
<br>
Lots of substituting can be done, but those are the classes you greatly prefer.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uzyphyr.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zyphyr</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 162<br> <font color=#333333>(3/28/02 12:13:20 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=176.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: What is the definition of  the &quot;Classic Group?&quot</span><hr size=1> The roles in a &quot;classic&quot; group (as I see it at least):<br>
<br>
-Tank :Warrior primarily, but Pally/SK are acceptable 2nd choices.<br>
<br>
-Healer :Cleric prefered, Shaman/Druid can be acceptable depending on the makeup of the rest of the party.<br>
<br>
-Backup Healer :Shaman/Druid, can be ommited in some cases - especially if you have a Pally as your tank since he can do some healing.<br>
<br>
-Crowd control :Enchanter, though Bards are also suitable. If you have a Shaman in your healing lineup for slows/haste, a Necro can do the job somewhat with Screaming Terror. If you have plenty of room to work and will not be facing casters, anyone with Root can do at least a little CC.<br>
<br>
-Damage Dealer *2 : Rogues and Monks are prefered. Any melee, wizards, necros, and mages all get picked for groups under this category. In groups where there is only 1 healer, the backup healer slot is replaced with a 3rd Damage Dealer.<br>
<br>
