<br>
Since the majority of characters are &quot;holy trinity&quot; characters, this group would be ideal for them to maximize experience in a fast pull dungeon environment<br>
<br>
Warrior<br>
Cleric<br>
Enchanter<br>
Shaman<br>
Rogue <br>
Monk<br>
<br>
That is your basic cookie cutter group.. as long as the break goes ok, you can theoretically grind out hour upon hour of repetitive and unimaginative xp.<br>
<br>
Everyone has one (1) specific role, and as long as that role is followed you're fine.. Monk is interchangable with snarer/evaccer, as a group with an enchanter shouldn't even want single pulls. <br>
<br>
If you were to ask the minority (hybrids and damage casters),<br>
you would find a different definition of an &quot;ideal group&quot;.<br>
<br>
