<br>
A stereotypical necro would describe his experience of a classic group as &quot;Me.&quot;<br>
<br>
My main point, is that a supposed &quot;classic&quot; group is an ideal that the classes not invited to the group (mages, necro, hybrids, druids, etc.) create to rationalize why they are lfg at the zone-in in Seb.<br>
<br>
To use Seb as an example, I tend to find that people waiting for a &quot;classic&quot; group tend to go LFG for a much longer time, while the B2 group is collecting as much xp as they can pull with whoever happened to be at the zoneline when they went in.<br>
